ln — create a symbolic link

SYNOPSIS
  ln -s TARGET LINK

DESCRIPTION
  Creates a symbolic link at LINK pointing to TARGET. Hard links are
  not supported (the OC managed filesystem has no inode-level
  duplication primitive); -s is mandatory.

ENCODING
  k.vfs encodes a symlink as a side file LINK.lnk whose body holds
  the target path. vfs.list hides the .lnk suffix; vfs.exists,
  vfs.open and friends transparently follow links up to 8 levels deep
  before giving up with "too many levels of symbolic links".

  Use vfs.is_symlink(path) and vfs.readlink(path) for explicit
  inspection. Removing a symlink with rm deletes the LINK.lnk file,
  not the target.

EXAMPLES
  ln -s /etc/themes/dark.lua /home/alex/theme.lua
  rm /home/alex/theme.lua          removes only the link, not /etc/...
